11
00:00:53,052 --> 00:00:55,785
KARL MARLANTES:
Coming home from Vietnam

12
00:00:55,885 --> 00:00:59,687
was close to as traumatic
as the war itself.

13
00:01:01,623 --> 00:01:04,589
For years, nobody talked
about Vietnam.

14
00:01:04,689 --> 00:01:05,889
(gunfire)

15
00:01:05,989 --> 00:01:07,657
(marching band playing)

16
00:01:07,757 --> 00:01:09,291
We were friends
with a young couple

17
00:01:09,391 --> 00:01:14,093
and it was only after 12 years
that the two wives were talking.

18
00:01:14,193 --> 00:01:17,561
Found out that we both had been
Marines in Vietnam.

19
00:01:17,661 --> 00:01:20,162
Never said a word about it.

20
00:01:20,262 --> 00:01:21,963
Never mentioned it.

21
00:01:22,063 --> 00:01:24,130
And the whole country
was like that.

22
00:01:25,732 --> 00:01:28,466
It was so divisive.

23
00:01:28,566 --> 00:01:33,500
And it's like living in a family
with an alcoholic father.

24
00:01:33,600 --> 00:01:35,935
(whispering):
"Shh, we don't talk about that."

25
00:01:36,035 --> 00:01:38,303
(gunfire)

26
00:01:38,403 --> 00:01:40,303
Our country did that
with Vietnam.

27
00:01:40,403 --> 00:01:43,138
It's only been very recently
that, I think,

28
00:01:43,238 --> 00:01:45,905
that, you know, the baby boomers
are finally starting to say,

29
00:01:46,005 --> 00:01:47,272
"What happened?

30
00:01:47,372 --> 00:01:48,706
What happened?"

