65
00:04:15,964 --> 00:04:20,399
And for those of us who suffered
because of Vietnam,

66
00:04:20,499 --> 00:04:24,734
that's been our quest
ever since.

67
00:04:24,834 --> 00:04:31,369
DYLAN:
♪ And it's a hard,
it's a hard, it's a hard ♪

68
00:04:31,469 --> 00:04:33,437
♪ It's a hard

69
00:04:33,537 --> 00:04:38,006
♪ It's a hard rain's
a-gonna fall ♪

70
00:04:38,106 --> 00:04:42,141
NARRATOR:
America's involvement in Vietnam
began in secrecy.

71
00:04:42,241 --> 00:04:47,143
It ended, 30 years later,
in failure,

72
00:04:47,243 --> 00:04:50,476
witnessed by the entire world.

73
00:04:50,576 --> 00:04:53,412
DYLAN:
♪ And what did you see,
my darling young one? ♪

74
00:04:53,512 --> 00:04:56,680
NARRATOR:
It was begun in good faith
by decent people

75
00:04:56,780 --> 00:04:59,347
out of fateful
misunderstandings,

76
00:04:59,447 --> 00:05:03,882
American overconfidence,
and Cold War miscalculation.

77
00:05:03,982 --> 00:05:09,318
And it was prolonged because it
seemed easier to muddle through

78
00:05:09,418 --> 00:05:12,452
than admit that it had been
caused by tragic decisions,

79
00:05:12,552 --> 00:05:15,586
made by five American
presidents,

80
00:05:15,686 --> 00:05:18,522
belonging to both
political parties.

81
00:05:18,622 --> 00:05:20,522
DYLAN:
♪ I saw a room full of men
with their hammers a-bleeding ♪

82
00:05:20,622 --> 00:05:22,423
NARRATOR:
Before the war was over,

83
00:05:22,523 --> 00:05:26,191
more than 58,000 Americans
would be dead.

84
00:05:26,291 --> 00:05:31,093
At least 250,000
South Vietnamese troops died

85
00:05:31,193 --> 00:05:33,694
in the conflict, as well.

86
00:05:33,794 --> 00:05:37,729
So did over a million
North Vietnamese soldiers

87
00:05:37,829 --> 00:05:39,295
and Viet Cong guerrillas.

88
00:05:39,395 --> 00:05:42,297
DYLAN:
♪ Sharp swords in the hands
of young children ♪

89
00:05:42,397 --> 00:05:44,598
♪ And it's a hard...

90
00:05:44,698 --> 00:05:47,733
NARRATOR:
Two million civilians,
north and south,

91
00:05:47,833 --> 00:05:49,699
are thought to have perished,

92
00:05:49,799 --> 00:05:53,235
as well as tens of thousands
more in the neighboring states

93
00:05:53,335 --> 00:05:55,137
of Laos and Cambodia.

94
00:05:55,237 --> 00:05:57,703
(helicopter blades whirring)

95
00:05:57,803 --> 00:06:01,938
For many Vietnamese,
it was a brutal civil war;

96
00:06:02,038 --> 00:06:05,406
for others, the bloody
climactic chapter

97
00:06:05,506 --> 00:06:09,007
in a century-old struggle
for independence.

98
00:06:09,107 --> 00:06:14,176
DYLAN:
♪ And what'll you do now,
my blue-eyed son? ♪

99
00:06:14,276 --> 00:06:16,610
NARRATOR:
For those Americans
who fought in it,

100
00:06:16,710 --> 00:06:19,579
and for those who fought against
it back home,

101
00:06:19,679 --> 00:06:23,180
as well as for those who merely
glimpsed it on the nightly news,

102
00:06:23,280 --> 00:06:26,981
the Vietnam War
was a decade of agony,

103
00:06:27,081 --> 00:06:32,584
the most divisive period
since the Civil War.

104
00:06:32,684 --> 00:06:37,552
Vietnam seemed to call
everything into question--

105
00:06:37,652 --> 00:06:42,087
the value of honor
and gallantry;

106
00:06:42,187 --> 00:06:46,722
the qualities of cruelty
and mercy;

107
00:06:46,822 --> 00:06:51,290
the candor of the
American government;

108
00:06:51,390 --> 00:06:55,160
and what it means
to be a patriot.

109
00:06:57,026 --> 00:07:01,595
DYLAN:
♪ Where hunger is ugly,
where the souls are forgotten ♪

110
00:07:01,695 --> 00:07:03,829
NARRATOR:
And those who lived through it

111
00:07:03,929 --> 00:07:06,829
have never been able
to erase its memory,

112
00:07:06,929 --> 00:07:09,998
have never stopped arguing
about what really happened,

113
00:07:10,098 --> 00:07:15,667
why everything went so badly
wrong, who was to blame,

114
00:07:15,767 --> 00:07:18,468
and whether it was all worth it.

115
